Results
In the 2011 survey (mean PM2.5: 40.6 $\mu$g/m3), exposure to PM2.5 in the preceding 1–2 months was associated with a 2.2% decrease (95% confidence interval [CI]: −4.1%, −0.3%) in FVC and a 2.3% decrease (95% CI: −4.0%, −0.5%) in FEV1. By contrast, a significant relationship between PM2.5 concentrations and lung function was not observed in the 2016–2017 survey (mean PM2.5: 30.0 $\mu$g/m3).
